	<h2><span><span class="conr">#1&nbsp;</span><a href="viewtopic.php?pid=595#p595">2009-01-23 01:57:44</a></span></h2>
	<div class="box">
		<div class="inbox">
			<div class="postleft">
				<dl>
					<dt><strong><a href="profile.php?id=90022">sren</a></strong></dt>
					<dd class="usertitle"><strong>Member</strong></dd>
					<dd class="postavatar"></dd>
				</dl>
			</div>
			<div class="postright">
				<h3>TopBT: a fast BitTorrent client to significantly save induced traffic</h3>
				<div class="postmsg">
					<p>Hi all,<br /><br />We previously posted here about our TopBT software in August 2008. Since then, we have been actively optimizing our code. Now we have re-implemented TopBT based on Vuze version 4.0.0.4. This new version TopBT v1.5 downloads faster than its previous version that was implemented on top of LH-ABC code base. Plus, it has a friendly interface showing the amount of Internet traffic it has saved. <br /><br />Our evaluation results from typical runs on Windows XP show that TopBT can achieve comparable download speed compared to the original Vuze and uTorrent, sometimes even faster. More importantly, it can save Internet traffic significantly, easily hits hundreds of mega bytes of traffic for a downloading file with size of 1G bytes. <br /><br />You all are very welcome to try out our Top-BT client, and give us some feedback. Currently the Top-BT client can be downloaded from two places:<br /><br /><a href="http://sourceforge.net/projects/top-bt/" rel="nofollow">http://sourceforge.net/projects/top-bt/</a><br /><a href="http://www.cse.ohio-state.edu/~sren/topbt/" rel="nofollow">http://www.cse.ohio-state.edu/~sren/topbt/</a><br /><br />Thank you!<br /><br />Best,<br />Shansi</p>
					<p class="postedit"><em>Last edited by sren (2009-01-23 02:00:39)</em></p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="clearer"></div>
